<subSubSection id="02C66578FFFEFFBFFF3D9ECA68437E27" pageId="19" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFEFFBFFF3D9ECA683F7FA7" blockId="19.[151,756,654,838]" pageId="19" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFEFFBFFF3D9ECA68057FC7" bold="true" box="[151,264,654,678]" pageId="19" pageNumber="33">Remarks:</emphasis>
It is characterized by a spinose test and elongate neck.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFEFFBFFF3D9E8A68437E27" blockId="19.[151,756,654,838]" pageId="19" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFEFFBFFF3D9E8A68CA7F87" bold="true" box="[151,455,718,742]" pageId="19" pageNumber="33">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is recorded in the Danian by SAID &amp; KENAWY (1956) and in the Paleocene zones by LUGER (1985). In the study area, it is recorded in the Paleocene zones.
</paragraph>
